    "summary": "Experienced lawyer with a recognized professional practice in the international legal field with a focus on victims\u2019 and survivors' rights (representation, participation and reparations), human rights, transitional justice and assistance to vulnerable individuals, families and communities. I have 15 years\u2019 experience working with victims of war crimes at the International Criminal Court and have carried out and led more than 25 field missions especially on the African continent, preparing and leading interviews with survivors. Before joining the International Criminal Court, I worked in Canada and Cambodia on projects in international justice, immigration and children\u2019s rights. \n\nI am a trained mediator and certified trainer (Avocats Sans Fronti\u00e8res France). Committed to safe and inclusive work environments through responsible leadership, mentoring and teamwork. Proficient in English and French. \n\n\nAreas of expertise: \n\u2022\tHolistic, survivor-centred and trauma-informed approaches to the assistance and representation of victims in international judicial proceedings. My practice is based on listening to victims\u2019 stories, identifying and understanding the traumas they experienced and their needs, supporting their resilience in order to help them re-envision their futures and advocating for their rights, integrating elements derived from psychology, communication, mediation, anthropology and forensics. \n\u2022\tSpecialized knowledge and experience in the support and representation of victims of sexual violence, vulnerable children and other marginalised groups, and in the development of reparations programs. \n\u2022\tDesign and delivery of training courses, guidelines and resources for lawyers, judges, prosecutors, police officers, NGO representatives, schools and universities on victims\u2019 rights. \n\u2022\tBuilding partnerships and collaboration with internal and external stakeholders.",
